author: @salmanurhaliza_2563
text:
Reff:
I’m ready to love
» Aku siap untuk mencintai
Naege malhae jwo
» Katakan padaku
Can we stay together, can we stay together?
» Bisakah kita tetap bersama, bisakah kita tetap bersama?
I’m a fool of love for you
» Aku begitu bodoh karena cinta padamu
Nae mameul ne gyeote forever, ne gyeote forever
» Hatiku akan selalu ada di sisimu, selamanya di sisimu

» Reff ini kembali menguatkan perasaan cinta yang mendalam dan keinginan untuk bersama selamanya.

Bait 1:
Neol manna nae maeumi
» Saat aku bertemu denganmu, hatiku
Gyesok deo jaraseo, hoo
» Terus berkembang semakin besar, hoo
Uri sairan chinguroneun
» Hubungan kita sebagai teman
Mojara nan
» Tak lagi cukup bagiku

» Bait pertama menggambarkan perasaan cinta yang semakin tumbuh setelah pertemuan dengan seseorang. Penyanyi merasa bahwa hubungan pertemanan saja tidak cukup lagi dan ingin sesuatu yang lebih dalam.

Pre-Reff:
Cheoeum neukkin simjangui sokdoga
» Detak jantungku yang pertama kali kurasakan
Iri ppareun jul mollasseo
» Tak kusangka akan berdegup secepat ini
All I wanna do is run away
» Yang kuinginkan hanyalah melarikan diri
Cause you are my escape, baby
» Karena kaulah pelarianku, sayang
Love has no limit daedabeul wonhae, ayy
» Cinta tak memiliki batas, aku ingin sebuah jawaban, ayy

» Pre-reff ini mengungkapkan betapa kuatnya perasaan cinta yang dirasakan penyanyi. Ia terkejut dengan seberapa cepat hatinya berdetak karena orang yang dicintainya dan ingin memastikan apakah perasaan itu berbalas.

» Reff ini menunjukkan kesiapan penyanyi untuk mencintai seseorang sepenuhnya. Ia ingin memastikan bahwa mereka bisa tetap bersama dan mengungkapkan betapa besarnya cintanya.

author: @francoisforever
text: damn, the simplicity of this stage though. minimal stage props and decorations, almost muted colored outfits and only one set. Yet their maturity and professionalism jumps out at you almost immediately. No need for flashy or ground-breaking camera work and bling, instead they utilized their greatest asset: their performance and charisma. The lighting also played a big part on the whole thing, making everything look aesthetically pleasing. The outfits were downright simple (Mingyu was only wearing a collared shirt and brown pants for goodness sake!😂) but suited their entire theme overall. What's even more impressive is that this was for the western audience, so you'd think they'd go extravagant but no. This is them, showing the market their core strength as a team, which is coordination, choreography, vocals, and performance without the distraction of over the top outfits, props and stage set. And I'd take that any day over any other performance.

author: @vnree
text:
I rly like the sequence around this part 1:15 

mingyu ended it. the lights dim down, some stuff got taken out from the song, it's a bit quieter now & sets up the next verse. vernon starts, the rest of them disperse & go into their positions, the spotlight shines on dino, alone during his part. the beat kinda picks up, more things get added in the song & the8 sings in such a heartfelt way about the *_feeling of his heart racing for the 1st time_* (which somehow kinda suits the song in terms of production too? idk, I put the explanation of what I'm thinking at the end in case anyone wants to read it, marked w an asterisk (*)). we cut back to mingyu, coming in pretty strong w his verse. as if he's now sure that this feeling that he's experiencing is truly love, he declares: *_'cause you are my escape_* & says *_just need you to be ready,_* bcs he's finally decided--firm in his decision to pursue love. joshua takes the center, followed by all the other members. *_ready to love_* starts

*the 1st time you fell in love w someone, your heart races (similar to how the beat picks up), you feel a lot of things & you're probably experiencing a lot of things for the 1st time as well (some more instruments/effects got added into the song if I understand correctly?)

this could be me just kinda reaching & trying to make sense of it all, but tbh it's just fun & interesting to think ab the song as a story, as well as see what's going on w the production & try to see how it suits the song. I feel like svt does this rly well
